in fibroblasts from Friedreich’s ataxia patient","issued":{"date-parts":[[2019]]},"DOI":"10.1590/fst.09919","container-title":"Food Science and Technology International","abstract":"Abstract Friedreich’s ataxia (FRDA) is a progressive neuromuscular disorder caused by substantial decrease of mitochondrial protein frataxin responsible for biogenesis of iron-sulphur clusters and protection from oxidative damage. In this study, we investigated the antioxidant activities of a standardized aqueous extract from fruiting bodies of Hericium erinaceus mushroom (HESAE) and its protective effects against oxidative damage induced by L-Buthionine sulfoximine (BSO) in fibroblasts derived from FRDA patient. The lactate dehydrogenase-based viability assay showed that FRDA fibroblast was sensitive to 12.5 mM BSO with a reduction of viability to 52.51 ± 13.92% after 24 h of BSO exposure. Interestingly, co-incubation with 32 mg/mL HESAE increased the viability to 85.35 ± 3.4%. Further, 12.5 mM BSO caused a decrease in the ratio of cellular reduced glutathione (GSH) to oxidised GSH (GSSG) that leads to cell death. Nevertheless, the damage was reduced by co-incubation with 32 mg/mL HESAE. Nuclear fluorescence staining revealed that 12.5 mM BSO induced cell death and the apoptosis was decreased by co-incubation with HESAE. These findings suggest the ability of HESAE in attenuating BSO-mediated cytotoxicity through maintenance of membrane integrity and optimal GSH/GSSG ratio, that are closely linked to its antioxidant activities. Further in vivo trials are highly warranted to clarify its potential benefits in management of FRDA.","tags":["#literature_note"],"author":[{"family":"Lew","given":"Sze Yuen","literal":""},{"family":"Lew","given":"Sze-Yuen","literal":""},{"family":"Yow","given":"Yoon-Yen","literal":""},{"family":"Yow","given":"Yoon-Yen","literal":""},{"family":"Lim","given":"Lee Wei","literal":""},{"family":"Lim","given":"Lee Wei","literal":""},{"family":"Wong","given":"Kah-Hui","literal":""},{"family":"Wong","given":"Kah-Hui","literal":""}],"citation-key":"lew_antioxidant-mediated_2019","year":"2019","dateCreated":"2026-03-31","reading-status":"to-read","aliases":["Antioxidant-mediated protective role of Hericium erinaceus (Bull.: Fr.) Pers. against oxidative damage in fibroblasts from Friedreich’s ataxia patient"],"author-links":["[[Author/Sze Yuen Lew]]","[[Author/Sze-Yuen Lew]]","[[Author/Yoon-Yen Yow]]","[[Author/Yoon-Yen Yow]]","[[Author/Lee Wei Lim]]","[[Author/Lee Wei Lim]]","[[Author/Kah-Hui Wong]]","[[Author/Kah-Hui Wong]]"],"attachment":["[[biblib/lew_antioxidant-mediated_2019/lew_antioxidant-mediated_2019.pdf|PDF]]"],"related":[[]]},"task_lines":[],"tasks":{},"codeblock_ranges":[],"last_embed":{"hash":"olosue","at":1774951887263}},"smart_blocks:Research/@lew_antioxidant-mediated_2019.md#---frontmatter---": {"path":null,"embeddings":{"TaylorAI/bge-micro-v2":{"vec":[-0.00601089,-0.0472225,0.02415608,-0.02556639,0.01796765,-0.00832165,0.02819151,0.03120467,-0.03253652,-0.08151941,0.0020193,-0.06246767,0.03369086,0.01167588,-0.02472669,0.0170859,0.0068877,0.02002387,-0.11467689,0.02980374,0.00785652,-0.00929303,0.03444717,-0.04181676,0.02013663,0.04663881,-0.00762645,0.02118748,-0.0674103,-0.2094918,-0.00551593,-0.04458266,0.00729278,-0.02203732,-0.04025999,0.02398574,0.01303336,-0.00698348,-0.00974411,-0.03761327,0.03508713,0.0654897,0.03155415,0.02496894,-0.01894731,-0.01064134,-0.01033547,-0.03296814,0.05269532,-0.02917066,-0.03412139,-0.01861564,0.0432138,0.01321662,0.06229603,0.03126798,-0.00563204,0.01986839,-0.01118547,0.0396397,0.02305424,0.04163131,-0.17093939,0.0632389,0.06952246,-0.01228084,-0.03326916,-0.04045262,0.10369065,0.01478431,-0.08495932,0.03255764,0.03479174,0.01896707,0.05888151,-0.02080157,-0.02141504,-0.06516746,0.01330665,0.01037747,0.02389866,0.02356066,0.02290367,0.04158839,0.00246043,-0.04498964,0.02297879,-0.08219319,0.01169598,-0.00470347,-0.00990146,-0.00933676,0.03062753,0.04256392,-0.06076993,0.00395